<p><div class="content-section-b" style="padding-left:15px;padding-right:15px; margin-top:-20px; ">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<h1 class="lead">DasData - Privacy  </h1>

            This document describes the information we collect and the ways we use that information.
            Note that information provided here is preliminary and is subject to change.
            <br/> <br/>
<strong>INFORMATION WE COLLECT </strong> <br/>

            DAS stores user IP when submits any form. This information is shared on notifications for the form owners.
            <br/>
            We don't store any other personal information other than phone number and email address of the user account.
            <br/>User access details are randomly generated when the account is created.<br/>
            We get visitor statistics in order to offer better service.<br/>
<br/>
<strong>INFORMATION SHARING</strong>
<br/>
            We do not share or sell your personal information for commercial purposes except to provide products or services you've requested, and only if we have your permission. <br/>
            We do not share or sell information submitted to our system through DasData that you create. <br/>
            We may share information <b>ONLY if complying with legal process</b>, preventing fraud or imminent harm, ensuring the security of our network and services.<br/>
<br/>
<strong>USE OR STORE COOKIES</strong><br/>
            User details are stored in temporary server sessions or in the local memory of the app.
            Other cookies are for devices configuration or for usage statistics.
            <br/>
<br/>
<strong>CHANGES </strong>
<br/>
            DasData may periodically update this policy. <br/> If it is significantly changed, we will notify you by email or by placing a prominent notice on our site.

            <br/>
<br/>
<strong>OTHER ISSUES</strong><br/>
            Send email to <a href="mailto:support@DasData.co">support@DasData.co</a> for any other issues and things that can concern your privacy regarding DasData.

        </div>
</div>
</div>
